snippet: Nasdaq OMX Group, the company that operates the Nasdaq stock exchange, benefited from increased revenue in its ancillary services.
abstract: Nasdaq OMX Group benefits in fourth quarter from increased revenue in its ancillary services; profit was $82 million, or 45 cents per share, down from $137 million, or 69 cents per share, in year-ago quarter; revenue rose to $422 million.
lead_paragraph: Nasdaq OMX Group, the company that operates the Nasdaq stock exchange, benefited from increased revenue in its ancillary services.

headline.seo: Profit at Nasdaq OMX Group Tops Expectations
